"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-adam-peaty-team-gb-swimming-paris-2024-b2522484.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Adam Peatysaid a new relaxed mindset can serve him well after securing passage to this summer's ParisOlympicsby finishing first in his signature 100m breaststroke event on the first day of the British Championships in London.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9978453504804166, \"rank\": 0.002158656171731859, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old touched the wall in 57.94 seconds in the evening's final - the fastest men's 100m breaststroke time in the world this year and an improvement on the 59.10 seconds it took him to win bronze at February's World Championships in Doha.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 815, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.978448011311691e-14, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, who still holds the world record of 56.88 seconds in the event, is now set to defend his back-to-back Olympic titles after securing a nomination in the British championships, one year after pulling out of the 2023 event to begin what became an extended mental health-motivated hiatus from the sport.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8095663676474184e-12, \"text\": \"British championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty said afterwards: \\\"I am not fully back, I have still got a second!\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's always going to be my mindset, but I have got a healthy approach to it.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A few years ago, I'd have come out of there disappointed.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have learned to appreciate the moments of greatness for myself.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For me, that was a great swim, executed well - but the most promising thing is that I am finding peace in the water now, instead of anger and just fighting it, and trying to win like that.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am finding a new version of myself which I am really liking, and I think that's a version that can do really well at the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The most direct way of securing aParis 2024nomination this week is to finish first in the open finals of each individual event, provided athletes clock in at or under a specific time set by the newly-rebranded Aquatics GB, though nominations are still subject to an official rubber-stamp by the British Olympic Association.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987225906981814, \"rank\": 0.0012664581674770644, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty emerged from his afternoon heat with a time of 58.53, the only man of 64 entrants in the event's heats to touch the wall in under a minute, marking another significant step on a comeback journey for the five-time Olympic medallist.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was sidelined from the 2022 World Championships due to a foot injury and last year withdrew from the British Championships, making his competitive return in Doha.\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.8095663676474184e-12, \"text\": \"British Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.978448011311691e-14, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a real win for my team, my family and myself,\\\" said Peaty.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have come through the past three years of hell.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not want to see a pool again.\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport had broken me.\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not know what route to go down and so many things got in my way.\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But now I am waking up each day and enjoying my job.\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who knows what the ending is going to be but I am having fun along the way.\\\"\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James Wilby, who finished second to Peaty, missed the 59.45sec nomination time by an agonising 0.02 seconds but could still be one of a maximum 30 swimmers nominated by Aquatics GB following the championships' conclusion on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0476956835428415e-15, \"text\": \"James Wilby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Wilby\"}, {\"begin\": 3027, \"end\": 3029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987225906981814, \"rank\": 0.0012664581674770644, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scotland's Keanna MacInnes, 22, punched her ticket after overtaking Laura Stephens in the women's 200m butterfly, though Stephens - the reigning world champion in the event - also finished below the required nomination time to put herself in contention forTeam GB.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3082, \"end\": 3090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5993828005546253, \"rank\": 0.4984700709788882, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3150, \"end\": 3164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Stephens\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Stephens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Stephens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Stephens\"}, {\"begin\": 3343, \"end\": 3345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987225906981814, \"rank\": 0.0012664581674770644, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Freya Colbert, 20, who claimed women's 400m individual medley gold in Doha, finished ahead of training partner Abbie Wood in the women's 200m freestyle to secure her nomination, while Wood's time was also under the nomination standard.\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\", \"score\": 0.9168684623515448, \"rank\": 0.08894892113098227, \"text\": \"Freya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\"}, {\"begin\": 3354, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999931583261, \"rank\": 6.841006343063994e-09, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 3418, \"end\": 3422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.978448011311691e-14, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}, {\"begin\": 3459, \"end\": 3469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abbie_Wood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abbie Wood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abbie_Wood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abbie_Wood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the first year the British Championships combined events for both para and non-disabled athletes, and it was Poppy Maskill who emerged with the top, sub-nomination standard time in the multi-classification women's para 200m freestyle where five athletes finished under the standard.\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bath-based Kieran Bird came close in the men's 400m freestyle, finishing in 3:45.63 - a hair off the required 3:45.43 - but might have also done enough do impress the selectors.\", \"from\": 3877, \"to\": 4054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"score\": 0.7531648145351793, \"rank\": 0.3196052416286691, \"text\": \"Kieran\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4107, \"end\": 4118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.930819489795211e-15, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"